<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,654,859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1562860211" country="Malta" location="North American" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Sardinia">
MALLORCA—Palma: Es Carnatge, 10.2015, 15 exx. on bushes of 
<taxonomicName box="[991,1181,690,715]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Atriplex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="halimus">
<emphasis box="[991,1181,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Atriplex halimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName box="[1233,1425,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Chenopodiaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chenopodiaceae</taxonomicName>
). This is an invading species of 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:312C87C80F4B2C66BBB51CEE025E702B:BC5A60050F4B2C66BACA1CB601A6719F" box="[488,670,726,751]" country="Malta" name="North American" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" stateProvince="Sardinia">North American</location>
origin which had been previously quoted from 
<collectingRegion box="[1202,1295,726,751]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Clark" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" refString="Clark, S. M., Rattu, A. &amp; Cillo, D. (2014) Monoxia obesula Blake, 1939, a species native to the U. S. A. and adventive to Sardinia, Italy (Coleoptera Chrysomelidae Galerucinae Galerucini). Zootaxa, 3774 (1), 83 - 89. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3774.1.6" type="journal article" year="2014">
Clark 
<emphasis box="[1380,1436,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[270,336,762,787]" name="Malta" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Malta</collectingCountry>
very recently (
<bibRefCitation author="Mifsud" box="[504,655,762,787]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" refString="Mifsud, D. (2016) A second Palaearctic record of Monoxia obesula (Coleoptera Chrysomelidae Galerucinae). Bulletin of Insectology, 69, 159 - 160." type="journal article" year="2016">Mifsud 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="158" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,654,859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Our citation is the third Palaearctic record of this species. The event has probably occurred by trade of ornamental plants.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
